## Superseded from config-linter-yaml-false-positive-fix

```yaml
name: config-linter-yaml-false-positive-fix
description: "Fix line-level YAML linter false positives by replacing a narrow key regex with an allowlist of valid YAML constructs and block scalar state tracking."
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-25
version: "1.0.0"
verification: verified-local
```

Fix YAML linter false-positive "Possible malformed key" warnings by replacing
`^\s*[\w\-]+:` with an allowlist covering quoted keys, flow mappings, list items,
timestamps, block scalars, and document separators. Add block scalar state tracking
(`in_block_scalar` + `block_scalar_indent`) to skip multi-line string contents.
Extract helpers to satisfy Ruff C901 complexity ‚â§10.

