## Superseded from json-schema-from-pydantic-models

```yaml
name: json-schema-from-pydantic-models
description: "Skill: json-schema-from-pydantic-models"
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-19
version: "1.0.0"
```

Derive JSON schemas from Pydantic models: read `models.py` first (authoritative), then
YAML config files (reality check). Use `oneOf` for nullable fields, `additionalProperties: false`
throughout, `examples` arrays for IDE support. Name test helper `check_schema` not `validate`.
Three schemas created: `defaults.schema.json`, `tier.schema.json`, `model.schema.json`.
38 tests. PR HomericIntelligence/ProjectScylla#1376, Issue #1357.

---

## Superseded from validate-config-name-family

```yaml
name: validate-config-name-family
description: "Skill: validate-config-name-family"
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-19
version: "1.0.0"
```

`validate_name_model_family_consistency()` ‚Äî checks `name` field contains the model
family (sonnet/haiku/opus) implied by the YAML filename. `KNOWN_FAMILIES: frozenset`,
`extract_model_family()` splits on `-`. Skip unknown families to avoid false positives
for non-Anthropic models. Loosen `== 1` ‚Üí `>= 1` in tests when a new validator adds
extra warnings. Issue #775, PR #821; 30 tests, 2239 total passing.

