## Superseded from validator-python-env-pyyaml-mismatch

```yaml
name: validator-python-env-pyyaml-mismatch
description: "Run a Python validation script when python3 fails with ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'yaml'."
category: tooling
date: 2026-04-03
version: "1.0.1"
verification: verified-local
```

`which -a python python3` to check interpreter divergence; `python3 -c 'import sys; print(sys.executable)'`
to identify which binary is failing. Use the conda-backed `python` when `python3` is Homebrew.
Never blindly install packages ‚Äî align interpreter first.

